# Add Master Data and Return Plan Views

This plan outlines the steps to allow the master manager to view the registered product master data and return plan data.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend ([main.py](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/main.py))
- **[MODIFY]** [main.py](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/main.py)
  - Add `GET /api/masters` endpoint to fetch [ProductMaster](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/models.py#5-12) records from the database.
  - Add `GET /api/plans` endpoint to fetch [ReturnPlan](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/models.py#13-20) records, with an optional `store` query parameter to filter by store (similar to the scans endpoint).

### Frontend ([templates/index.html](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/templates/index.html))
- **[MODIFY]** [templates/index.html](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/templates/index.html)
  - In the Master Dashboard (`#view-dashboard`), add a tab navigation menu to switch between three views: "스캔 내역" (Scan History), "상품 마스터" (Product Master), and "반품 예정 리스트" (Return Plan).
  - Add table containers for the new "상품 마스터" and "반품 예정 리스트" views.

### Frontend ([static/js/app.js](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/static/js/app.js))
- **[MODIFY]** [static/js/app.js](file:///c:/Users/dkstk/.gemini/antigravity/static/js/app.js)
  - Add logic to handle switching between the dashboard tabs.
  - Create `loadMasterData()` function to fetch data from `/api/masters` and render it into the product master table.
  - Create `loadPlanData()` function to fetch data from `/api/plans` and render it into the return plan table.
  - Update the initialization logic so that the default tab is active when the manager logs in.

## Verification Plan

### Local Verification
1. Run the FastAPI server: `uvicorn main:app --reload`
2. Open the browser and enter the system as a "마스터 관리자".
3. Upload sample Excel files for the Product Master and Return Plan (if the database is currently empty).
4. Click through the new tabs ("스캔 내역", "상품 마스터", "반품 예정 리스트").
5. Verify that the correct data is fetched from the server and displayed cleanly in the tables for each tab.
